HEADWORD: Contravallation
<hw>Con`tra*val*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>contra-</ets> + <ets>vallation</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>contrevallation</ets>. Cf. <er>Countervallation</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A trench guarded with a parapet, constructed by
besiegers, to secure themselves and check sallies of the
besieged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Contravene</ent>⟦br⟧
